        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 2 at 3:30PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 329 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of June Lake, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Agnew Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
